Police in Kwale have shot dead a man suspected to be a thief at Mwambeni area of Matuga subcounty. The deceased is said to have attacked police officers who were on foot patrol with a knife after they ordered him to stop. Matuga subcounty police commander Gababa Darso confirmed the incident that happened on Thursday afternoon. “Police officers who were on patrol attempted to stop the middle-aged man who looked suspicious but he removed a knife from his waistband and started attacking them,” Darso said. “He refused to stop when asked and removed a knife and started charging at them. They shot him,” he said. Darso said police were investigating the incident, adding that no police officer was injured in the confrontation. Darso said when the man refused to stop an officer fired once, hitting the man who fell dead at the scene.